    whySearch: `Strong CFO candidates are among the most passively employed executives in the UK market. A CFO who is performing well, has the confidence of the CEO and audit committee, and is well-compensated has every reason to stay and almost no incentive to engage with unsolicited approaches from unknown recruiters. Reaching the best CFO candidates — those who are settled, performing, and not actively looking — requires a search firm with genuine relationships in the financial leadership market, the credibility to make a compelling first approach, and the sector knowledge to position the opportunity in a way that makes the disruption of a move genuinely worthwhile.`,
