    whySearch: `The best CTOs are embedded in technically interesting work, surrounded by engineers who respect them, and receiving regular unsolicited approaches that they largely ignore. Reaching them requires more than a LinkedIn message — it requires a search consultant who can have a technically credible conversation, a well-articulated account of the opportunity, and a relationship-based approach that distinguishes genuine executive search from the background noise of recruitment outreach. The technology talent market is uniquely competitive; executive search firms with genuine technology sector relationships consistently outperform general recruiters by a significant margin for CTO and VP Engineering appointments.`,
